Famous Nigerian dancer and choreographer, Kafayat Oluwatoyin Shafau aka Kaffy has asserted that she has continued to thrive in every area of her life despite betrayals and pains. The single mother of two made this known on an Instagram live noting that she has been on a healing journey for the past five years.   EMEKA OKORO: My faith determines role I play     Toyin Abraham, Okanlawon feature in The Stranger I Know     My relationship with Basketmouth, by Lisa Viola   She said “It’s very important to be grateful, do you know that in all the pain and betrayal I have gone through, I have always been winning. I have always been surrounded by love, growth, career upliftment, and beautiful people. Pain is devastating, betrayal, divorce, I have gone through all of this so those of you that know my story, pain is so devastating that people that are causing you pain do not realize that they don’t even realize how much it is. There are some pains I have felt for some people I don’t even pray it back for them if they were the one receiving it, they would have died but God himself pruned me.” In January 2022, the 42-year-old opened up about her divorce and other issues in her marriage after publishing a book on her life and marriage.